The arrangement was such that one legion (probably the ldth) formed the right wing, two legions the centre, and one legion the left wing; the legions were in the same line. This is of importance, because the triple line of Caesar is commonly misunderstood; ii the legion is considered as the tactical unit, there is but one line ; but the cohorte of each legion were arranged in three lines. The celebrated triplex acies is, then, the order oi battle, according to which the ten cohorts, of which each legion was made up, were stationed in three lines, one behind the other ; ordinarily four beingin the front line, three in the second, and three in the third, a suitable space being left between the cohorts.
